result.name: Curry House Coco Ichibanya

reviews.text: One of my favorite places. Not quite as good as in Japan but pretty close. I get the fried pork curry. I love spicy food and this is one of the few places that is actually spicy.

I am eating here right now and the curry tastes like it's from a box. This is nothing like the actual Coco Curry in Japan. Plus, they don't let you add toppings to certain dishes, which is ridiculous. It was a waste of money. You can get better curry from a box at SOGO.

Ok service, food came suspiciously quickly. 
I got the chicken katsu curry and it came around 5 minutes after ordering. I started to eat the chicken, and around 2 pieces in, I see that the chicken is kind of undercooked, and almost entirely pink in the middle. I didn't eat much of the meat after that, but at least the rice and curry are ok?
Also got the iced milk tea. It's mediocre, you get the creamer and sugar syrup seperate from the tea.
There are better Coco Curry Houses in Asia, go to Japan, they at least cook the meat properly.

I like the curry a lot but i wouldn't recommend getting the milk tea. Another great thing is that you can choose how much rice you want and the spiciness of your curry. The place is great and family friendly they have a kid's menu and the place is very spacious. Overall, I think I would come back!
I love Coco Ichi curry. My favorite is spinach and cheese, rice 200g, hot level 3, additional curry source.

reviews.text: Comfort food with consistent quality.  This place never disappoints.
Comfortable place with nice food🤩
Great Japanese curry taste. Customisable extras including rice portion, spiciness and additional tasty sides. Service is OK but not too quick. The restaurant is usually very busy at lunch time.

Great food but absolutely clueless staff at the Hysan Place outlet. You’re better off walking 5 mins to Windsor House and having food there. Our drinks weren’t served half way thru our main meal....hurricane potatoes never showed up and had to be cancelled! When enquiring for either of the above...the standard answer from the waiter was...”We’re making it.”

Avoid the Hysan Place outlet if possible...been here a couple of times and never a good experience!
Fast food curry style. There's a number of customisation options for rice, spiciness and for the 'toppings' (like additional chicken, squid) on your curry.
